	Pros 

	open source

	supports multiple programming languages
	java , c#, .net,python perl ruby perl php javascript

	supports all the platforms/OS
	windows, macos, linux , unix

	Cross browser testing
	chrome FF Safari Edge Opera

	Headless browsers
	PhantomJs, HTMLUnitDriver Chrome Headless

	can be integrated with any open source unit testing framework
	such as Testng,JUnit -- TDD

	BDD Frameworks
	Cucumber, JBehave and  Serenity

	Light Weight
	Available in the form of APIS

	CI-CD

	Jenkins

	can be executed on local machine , cloud/VM/Servers

	BrowserStack SauceLabs AWS Docker

	Customize webdriver codebase -- source code will be shared

	Wrappers -- Appium, Protractor, Watir, Robot Framework.


	Cons

	1.as it is open source, no direct support.

	2.you need to learn programming  -- No scriptless or codeless Automation.

	3.no desktop app auotmation support.

	4.no report for test results.

	5.for any extra work: test cases designing, report, build, CI-CD.

	6.no bar code and no captcha.



